<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: OXNARD; 
</P>
<P>
SCHOOL DISTRICT TO RAISE LUNCH PRICES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GERRY BRAILO SPENCER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The price of school lunches will increase 25% in the Ocean View Elementary 
School District this fall because the schools are receiving less surplus food 
from the U.S. Department of Agriculture, board members said. 
</P>
<P>
The Board of Education of the four-school Oxnard district voted Tuesday to 
raise the price from $1 to $1.25. 
</P>
<P>
June Tanaka, a past president of the Laguna Vista Elementary School Parent 
Teachers Club and a cashier in a school cafeteria, said 85% of the students at 
the school are military dependents whose parents work at the Point Hueneme 
naval base. 
</P>
<P>
"Many of those children receive free lunches or buy reduced lunches for 40 
cents, a price mandated by the state," she said. "It's unfortunate, but the 
children who can afford lunches will pay the increase." GERRY BRAILO SPENCER 
</P>
</TEXT>
