<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTH BAY DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: NEALIS APPOINTED CITY MANAGER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Craig R. Nealis, deputy city administrator of Bellflower, has been appointed 
city manager of Rolling Hills. 
</P>
<P>
Nealis, 32, succeeds Terrence Belanger, who resigned in June to become 
assistant city manager of Diamond Bar. 
</P>
<P>
Nealis joined Bellflower in 1984 as an administrative assistant. He was 
assistant to the city administrator before being elevated to deputy city 
administrator in 1988. He holds degrees from the University of Nevada, Reno, 
and USC. 
</P>
<P>
Nealis, who will assume his Rolling Hills duties Aug. 27, will be paid $52,260 
a year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
