<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEOPLE IN THE NEWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dr. Gary S. Rinzler has been named medical director of rehabilitation services 
at San Pedro Peninsula Hospital. The center offers specialized care for 
strokes, spinal cord and brain injuries, severe pain disorders, and other 
neurologic and orthopedic problems. Rinzler previously was associate medical 
director of the Rehabilitation Institute of New Orleans at F. Edward Hebert 
Hospital. He has also been medical director of the Gulf Coast Regional Spinal 
Cord Injury Program. 
</P>
<P>
James Heinselman has returned as president of Harbor College. He left that post 
in early 1989 to serve for 17 months as acting vice chancellor of educational 
services for the Los Angeles Community College District. Heinselman was given 
the temporary assignment to help reorganize and decentralize the district's 
educational and business services divisions. 
</P>
<P>
Six men and women have been honored by the Black Faculty and Staff Assn. at Los 
Angeles Harbor College. Nina Simmons, a business administration major from 
Carson, and Debbie White, a nursing student from San Pedro, received the 1990 
Frederick Douglass Scholarship; James M. Rosser, president of Cal State Los 
Angeles, the 1990 Educational Leadership Award; Harold Daniels, a Harbor 
College professor of physical education, the Outstanding Faculty Award, and Al 
Swift of Carson, a technology department tool keeper, the Outstanding 
Classified Staff Award. A special award was presented posthumously to Nathan 
Banks, former chairman of the college's division of physical science and 
engineering. The award was accepted by Banks' wife, Davrye. 
</P>
<P>
Kevin M. Peterson of Palos Verdes Estates has been elected president of the 
Palos Verdes Peninsula Rotary Club, replacing Eric Allan, who will serve as 
immediate past president. Peterson, South Bay district president for GTE 
California, is immediate past president of the Torrance Area Chamber of 
Commerce. Also elected to the Rotary board were Gary Tossell, president-elect; 
John Schuricht, secretary; Linda Elliott, treasurer, and Dr. Ian Jones, vice 
president for programs. Other new board members are Russ Gagliano, Scott Magee, 
Tim Dickens, Ben Loughrin, Leo Trujillo, Tom Barnett, Denny Gillard, Allan 
Colman and Ed Clay. 
</P>
<P>
Irving T. Waaland of Palos Verdes Estates has received the American Defense 
Preparedness Assn.'s Simon Award for outstanding work in the design and 
development of advanced weapons systems, in particular the U.S. Air Force's B-2 
(Stealth) bomber. Waaland is vice president and chief designer for Northrop 
Aircraft Division. 
</P>
</TEXT>
