<HEADLINE>
<P>
KENNETH MICHAEL; RETIRED MAINTENANCE WORKER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Kenneth Michael of Burbank, who was a retired maintenance worker with the city 
of Burbank, has died at the Medical Center of North Hollywood. He was 76. 
</P>
<P>
Born in Chico, Calif., Michael died Friday of complications due to asthma, said 
his daughter-in-law, Arlene Kinzel. 
</P>
<P>
Michael was a member of the American Legion Post 15 and the Disabled American 
Veterans, having served in the U.S. Army from 1941 to 1945. 
</P>
<P>
He lived in the same house in Burbank for 44 years and began working for the 
city of Burbank in 1950. He retired in 1974. 
</P>
<P>
He is survived by his wife of 45 years, Lorna Michael; stepson Jack Kinzel of 
Simi Valley; seven grandchildren and 10 great grandchildren. 
</P>
<P>
A funeral service will be held today at 11:30 a.m. at Pierce Brothers Valhalla, 
10621 Victory Blvd., North Hollywood, which is handling the arrangements. 
Donations can be made in Michael's name to the American Lung Assn. 
</P>
</TEXT>
