<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ten cities have filed formal applications for the next two NHL expansion 
franchises. 
</P>
<P>
Eight U.S. cities -- Milwaukee, Seattle, San Diego, Phoenix, Houston, Miami, 
Tampa and St. Petersburg, Fla., and two Canadian entries, Hamilton and Ottawa, 
Ontario -- submitted applications and the $100,000 filing fee, $65,000 of which 
is refundable. The two teams accepted into the league will pay a $50-million 
franchise fee. 
</P>
<P>
The NHL is expected to announce its choices in December. 
</P>
