<P>
CLARE COMPLEX DEDICATED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The CLARE Foundation last week formally dedicated its new adult recovery home 
complex at 1865 9th St. 
</P>
<P>
The complex consists of a new dormitory-style building with 20 beds, and two 
renovated buildings on adjacent property. One of the buildings is for support 
staff, the other, an apartment-style building, houses another 20 residents. 
</P>
<P>
The CLARE Foundation is a nonprofit, community-based agency partially funded by 
the Los Angeles Office of Alcohol Programs and the city of Santa Monica. The 
agency has 14 programs, including a recovery home for men, women and children, 
a facility for the deaf, and drop-in centers. 
