<HEADLINE>
<P>
TRIAL ORDERED ON RAPE CHARGES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A former nurse's aide at a Glendale nursing home was ordered to stand trial 
Tuesday on charges that he raped and sodomized an elderly patient while working 
at the facility. 
</P>
<P>
Glendale Municipal Judge Charles E. Horan found that there was sufficient 
evidence to try Roy Alton Seaton, 45, of Burbank, on charges of sodomy, rape 
with a foreign object and sexual battery. 
</P>
<P>
Seaton, who is in County Jail, will be arraigned Aug. 29 in Pasadena Superior 
Court. 
</P>
<P>
Seaton was arrested June 28 after a nursing supervisor at Autumn Hills 
Convalescent Home allegedly caught him sexually assaulting an 82-year-old woman 
who had Alzheimer's disease. He was later fired. 
</P>
<P>
Investigators told Autumn Hills officials that Seaton was convicted in 1983 of 
lewd conduct with a child. 
</P>
<P>
In July, Los Angeles County officials levied an $11,000 fine against the home 
because the victim allegedly suffered physical and sexual abuse and because 
administrators allegedly failed to check the employee's background. 
</P>
