<HEADLINE>
<P>
CALIFORNIA IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
MOUNTAIN VIEW; 
</P>
<P>
SANTA CLARA COUNTY ENDING MEDFLY WAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Santa Clara County is moving into the final stage of its yearlong fight against 
an infestation of Mediterranean fruit flies. The last of nearly 800 million 
sterile Medflies were released from the Mountain View area last Friday, and 
about 1,200 new traps have been hung throughout the 65-square-mile quarantine 
area. If no fertile Medflies are trapped in the next few weeks, the quarantine 
that has blocked the shipment of fruits and vegetables from the area could be 
lifted by mid-September, said Greg Van Wassenhove, the county's agricultural 
commissioner. 
</P>
</TEXT>
