Insurer Backs Down: ITT Hartford Insurance Group said it would continue to 
write auto insurance policies, bowing to a threat from New Jersey state 
officials. ITT was attempting to withdraw from the New Jersey auto insurance 
market in reaction to Gov. Jim Florio's auto insurance reforms. The program 
forces the industry to pay nearly half of a $3-billion debt incurred by a 
state-run pool that covers high-risk drivers. 
