<P>
Mexico Guilty of 'Dumping' Cement: The U.S. International Trade Commission has 
imposed higher import duties on Mexican cement after finding that Cementos 
Mexicanos (Cemex) and other manufacturers were guilty of "dumping" cement on 
the U.S. market at artificially low prices. According to government estimates, 
Mexico exported $111 million in gray portland cement and clinker, the two 
concrete components covered by the ruling. Cemex has said it will appeal the 
decision. 
