<P>
General Homes Seeks Bankruptcy Protection: The Houston-based builder, once one 
of the biggest home builders in the nation, has filed for protection from 
creditors and reorganization under Chapter 11 of the federal bankruptcy code. 
</P>
<P>
The move is in response to an involuntary bankruptcy petition filed against the 
firm July 10 by three creditors claiming they were owed $561,400 in interest 
payments. General's corporate debt of $365 million includes $225 million owed 
to senior lenders and $140 million owed other creditors. General's mortgage 
company, FGMC Inc., is not affected by the filing. 
</P>
