<TEXT>
<P>
Charles H. Keating Jr. has caught up on late mortgage payments to avert 
foreclosure and an auction of his million-dollar suburban home, a spokesman 
said. 
</P>
<P>
The chairman of financially beleaguered American Continental Corp. "was able 
through gifts from friends to make the necessary payments and bring the 
mortgage up to where it is current," company spokesman Brad Boland said. Boland 
didn't disclose the amount of the payment. 
