<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: NEWPORT BEACH; 
</P>
<P>
POLICE IDENTIFY SHOOTING VICTIM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MATT LAIT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man found shot to death in a Newport Beach townhouse on Tuesday has been 
identified as Roger Hughes, 42, of Long Beach. 
</P>
<P>
Helen S. Parser, 49, was arrested on suspicion of murdering Hughes and is being 
held on $250,000 bail, Police Sgt. Andy Gonis said. 
</P>
<P>
Hughes and Parser were married in 1984, but police were uncertain about their 
recent marital status. "It's unclear if they had since been divorced," Gonis 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Gonis said police were alerted to the shooting by a "friend of the suspect's 
who called 911." 
</P>
<P>
When police arrived at the townhouse, on a bluff above Coast Highway, they 
surrounded the building and ordered Parser out of her home. She surrendered 
without incident. 
</P>
<P>
Gonis said it appeared that there had been a struggle between Parser and Hughes 
before the shooting. "The house was in disarray," he said. 
</P>
<P>
Parser was taken to a local hospital for examination of some minor bruises, but 
Gonis said she appeared to be in good condition. MATT LAIT 
</P>
</TEXT>
