<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: RETAIL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Chris Woodyard Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
6 New Wet Seals: Wet Seal, the high-fashion store for women, continues to grow. 
</P>
<P>
The chain said it opened six new stores this month, including a newly expanded 
outlet at the Orange Mall. 
</P>
<P>
Three of its new stores are in Florida, where the chain's officials are hoping 
that the store's youthful appeal and sunbaked image will catch on. They also 
have new stores in Hawaii and in Victorville. 
</P>
<P>
Wet Seal, founded as a little Balboa Island shop in the 1950s, has opened five 
other locations since March and expanded three others. The openings come on the 
heels of Wet Seal's initial public stock offering in July. The company raised 
about $43 million in the offering, which it is using to repay loans, upgrade 
the company's computer system, and expand its Irvine distribution center and a 
number of stores. 
</P>
</TEXT>
