<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: DIAMOND BAR; 
</P>
<P>
VOTE DELAYED ON TRASH PLAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council on Tuesday postponed for 90 days a decision on whether to 
franchise the city's residential garbage collection. 
</P>
<P>
After hearing testimony from nearly two dozen residents, the council chose to 
wait until November to make a decision. 
</P>
<P>
Assistant City Manager Terry Belanger said the council will "step back and take 
a little bit of a break, a breather" before deciding whether the city should go 
from its current open market status, in which residents can choose their own 
garbage haulers, to a franchise, in which one or more companies would have 
exclusive hauling rights within the city. 
</P>
</TEXT>
