<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: EL MONTE; 
</P>
<P>
PARKING TIME LIMIT LIFTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Shoppers can take their time and not worry about parking tickets since the City 
Council voted Tuesday to remove the two-hour time limit on city lots on the 
north and south sides of the Valley Mall between Granada Avenue, Ramona and 
Valley boulevards. 
</P>
<P>
The change was made after a request from the Downtown El Monte Business Assn. 
The two-hour limit will still apply to street parking on Valley Mall Boulevard. 
The ban on parking between 3 and 5 a.m. will continue. 
</P>
</TEXT>
