<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: MONTEREY PARK; 
</P>
<P>
LARGER FREEWAY SIGNS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Businesses near the freeway can advertise with taller and larger signs, the 
City Council decided Monday. 
</P>
<P>
There had been no special allowances for freeway signs. Under the new rules, 
businesses within 500 feet of a freeway can erect signs up to 50 feet tall and 
300 square feet in size. The businesses must be below or at the same level as 
the freeway. 
</P>
<P>
Signs must be more than 100 feet from residential areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
