<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: WEST COVINA; 
</P>
<P>
MALL DEVELOPERS SOUGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
City officials are seeking developers to renovate a 33-year-old mall into a 
high-volume retail shopping center. 
</P>
<P>
The Redevelopment Agency on Monday unanimously approved a request to begin 
soliciting proposals from developers for the Eastland Center shopping mall on 
the San Bernardino Freeway at Barranca Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
The agency wants developers to lure customers from throughout the San Gabriel 
Valley with multimedia advertising. Each proposal is expected to include the 
entire 57 acres of Eastland Center. The agency, however, will have the right to 
consolidate, mix or match proposals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
