<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: DUARTE; 
</P>
<P>
RULES FOR CAMPAIGN SIGNS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
There will be fewer legal places to put campaign signs in November, and it will 
cost more to ignore the rules under a new ordinance given preliminary approval 
by the City Council on Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
The ordinance amends the current sign ordinance, which prohibits posting on any 
public facilities, to include trees and poles within public facilities. 
</P>
<P>
The fee for violations has been increased from $5 to $10 for each sign removed 
by the city. 
</P>
<P>
A public hearing is scheduled for the Aug. 28 meeting, after which the council 
will make its final decision. If adopted, the ordinance will affect the 
November elections. 
</P>
</TEXT>
