<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: SIERRA MADRE; 
</P>
<P>
UPDATE FOR MUNICIPAL CODE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council on Tuesday took the first step toward recodifying the aging 
Municipal Code by voting to notify bidders who specialize in updating city 
ordinances. 
</P>
<P>
Recodification is necessary to clarify ambiguities of technical definitions, 
eliminate loopholes and standardize regulations that have been changed over the 
years, Mayor George Maurer said. 
</P>
<P>
The Municipal Code was last recodified in the late 1960s, Maurer said. 
</P>
<P>
City Manager James McRea said the cost of updating the Municipal Code could 
approach $10,000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
