<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: EL MONTE; 
</P>
<P>
HOME IMPROVEMENT GRANTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council increased limits on residential rehabilitation grants from 
$2,000 to $3,000, with some exceptions to be as high as $5,000. 
</P>
<P>
The grants are used to improve single-family homes and mobile homes, often 
owned by elderly, disabled or handicapped residents. The program is funded by 
Community Development Block Grant money. 
</P>
<P>
Planning Director Harold Johanson noted in a memorandum that neighboring cities 
have higher limits: In Arcadia, the limit is $7,000; in Covina, $6,000, and in 
San Dimas, $5,000. 
</P>
<P>
The council authorized the program administrator to grant case-by-case 
extensions of up to $5,000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
