NAMES IN THE NEWS; 
</P>
<P>
ROSS PEROT STILL RICHEST TEXAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FROM TIMES WIRE SERVICES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DALLAS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
H. Ross Perot is still the ultimate rich Texan. He retained his ranking as the 
wealthiest man in the state with a fortune estimated at $3 billion, according 
to Texas Monthly's list of the 100 richest Texans. 
</P>
<P>
Perot was followed by Dallas financier Harold Clark Simmons, who is worth $1.7 
billion, and five members of the Bass family of Ft. Worth, who own a combined 
$5.8 billion. The youngest person on the list is Michael Dell, 25, of Austin, 
the founder of Dell Computer Corp., who is worth $140 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
