<HEADLINE>
<P>
SHORT TAKES; 
</P>
<P>
'SOUND OF MUSIC' RELEASE SET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FROM TIMES WIRE SERVICES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
To celebrate the silver anniversary of "The Sound of Music," 20th Century Fox 
will re-release the Oscar-winning musical on Aug. 24, the studio announced 
Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
Winner of five Academy Awards, "The Sound of Music" made its debut in 1965 and 
was a commercial hit, grossing $57 million over an unprecedented 4 1/2-year 
run. 
</P>
<P>
The soundtrack album, featuring Julie Andrews, sold 10 million copies 
worldwide. 
</P>
<P>
The film will be re-released in Los Angeles and New York only. 
</P>
<P>
In addition to Miss Andrews, "The Sound of Music" stars Christopher Plummer and 
Eleanor Parker. The Rodgers-Hammerstein musical follows a singing family in 
war-torn Austria. 
</P>
<P>
The Aug. 23 gala party will be attended by Andrews, the film's director, Robert 
Wise, and six of the actors who played children in the film. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Julie Andrews 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
