<P>
BROWNS TO SIGN EX-JETS QB RYAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FROM TIMES WIRE SERVICES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MENTOR, Ohio 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Quarterback Pat Ryan, released by the New York Jets after 12 years with the 
team, is expected to sign today with the Cleveland Browns. 
</P>
<P>
Ryan, 34, worked out with the Browns on Wednesday and will sign a two-year deal 
if he passes a physical exam today. 
</P>
<P>
"We are waiting for the results of the physical," Browns' spokesman Bob Eller 
said. "It's likely we will sign him." 
</P>
<P>
With the Jets, Ryan played mostly as a reserve, most recently behind Ken 
O'Brien. He was released in the off-season after the Jets signed Tony Eason. 
</P>
</TEXT>
