<P>
JAPAN BEATS U.S. IN VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FROM TIMES WIRE SERVICES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TOYAMA, Japan 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Japan defeated the United States, 15-2, 15-11, 15-9, today in the opening match 
of a series of three women's volleyball matches in Japan. 
</P>
<P>
Motoko Ohbayashi scored nine points for Japan while Ruth Lawanson led the 
American team with five. 
</P>
<P>
The second match is to be held in Fukui, in northern Japan, on Saturday. 
</P>
