<HEADLINE>
<P>
DICKERSON WINS GREYHOUND STAKE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SPRINGFIELD, Ill. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dickerson turned just his fourth start into an impressive finish, winning the 
$110,000 Review Greyhound Stake for harness horses at the Illinois State 
Fairgrounds. 
</P>
<P>
In another major race Wednesday at the fairgrounds, Mantese destroyed the 
stakes record in winning the $74,000 Little Pat Review Stake for 2-year-old 
pacers. 
</P>
<P>
Dickerson, a victim of a break in his second-place elimination-heat finish, 
thundered home in the raceoff, winning for driver Jan Nordin in 1:58.1. The 
2-year-old trotting colt returned $12.80, $7.80 and $3.20. 
</P>
<P>
The Super Bowl colt had made just three official starts, winning one, before 
Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
Mantese won the Little Pat race-off in 1:53.45, shattering the previous record 
of 1:55.3 set last year by Till We Meet Again. 
</P>
</TEXT>
